article.headline: Bison upset No. 2 seed Delaware St. in MEAC tourney
article.linkText: Howard shocks No. 2 seed Delaware St. in MEAC
article.story:
RICHMOND, Va. (AP) -- Kyle Williams scored five of his 15 points
in overtime Wednesday night and Howard upset second-seeded Delaware
State 68-65 to advance to the semifinals of the Mid-Eastern
Athletic Conference tournament.

	   The Bison (13-16), seeded seventh, took the lead for good on
Williams' 3-pointer with 47 seconds left in overtime. It was his
only 3-pointer and just the third for Howard.

	   Delaware State (15-12) pulled within 64-63 when Aaron Matthews
made 2-of-4 free throws over the next 21 seconds, but Williams made
two free throws with 25 seconds left and Ron Williamson added two
more with 16 seconds to play for the Bison.

	   Howard was 7-for-8 from the foul line in the overtime.

	   Louis Ford led Howard with 18 points.

	   Carlos Hawkins had 14 and James Bowen 11 for the Hornets.
Matthews scored eight, including a dunk with 21 seconds in
regulation that forced the overtime tied at 56.

	   Howard will next play top-seeded South Carolina State, which
beat Bethune-Cookman 75-73 in the earlier game Wednesday, in the
semifinals on Friday.
